description:
The Creators | No. 5 | Bartholomew

The Creators series explores the human tendency to perceive life-like beings from within abstract forms. The images created here are made from millions of tiny particles following movement patterns based on the physarum slime mold. By trying different techniques for how the initial particles are placed, and by creating symmetry through mirroring, many different interesting life-like patterns can emerge.

Artist: Daniel Sierra | @dbsierra4444
